			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>OK, had a Necro that rather blatantly KSd me tonight twice.  Nothing I could do about it as he was level 65 and I was on my lil 55 BL.  I did send him a tell asking him to stop.  In the ensuing conversation with that unmitigated pile of fecal material he pulled the KSers last line of Defense.  HE claimed that he had talked to the server's Lead GM and that there was a difference between Agro and Engagement.  He claimed that you have to actually do damage (no SLows, snares and Debuffs don't count mind you) to have a claim to a mob.  Has anyone heard of this before?
<br />

<br />
My understanding from ages ago (couple years) was that first agro=right to kill, Even if the Mob agroes on you. My understanding as a result of this was that you basically coudln't take a mob off another to save their life UNLESS they asked for it. Anyone have any Links/sights/whatever proof at this is or isn't the case?
<br />

<br />
Thanks!
<br />

<br />
Tenosh 66 bard, Tahnel 55 BL.</span></td>
