				<td colspan="2"><span>in my experience they usually follow ... drumroll, common sense. As in: If two raids, two groups etc are ready to kill something using whatever tactic they want, like kiting something until its slowed and what not, the person/raid/group who engages has 'mob rights''
<br />

<br />
Sometimes, especially if there are raids involed it can be complicated for mr GM so they come up with excuses like whats been posted. Plus, how often do they <b>know</b> what happened? 
<br />
Since Gore is used as example, long time ago when gore was a real raid mob the GM simply told both raids werent allowed to go anywhere near her until he rolled for it. Even though my raid was ready to kill her and the other raid wasnt even buffed plus we were there long before them we still lost because the other raid petitioned. The GM didn't really do anything wrong because he couldnt possibly know everything so he rolled.
<br />

<br />
For raids they -usually- do first in force with a personal touch depending on GM. Once the other guild lost because they slipped and said they were ready when they werent so the GM told them to engage within two minutes or he'd port them out and well, they got ported out.
<br />

<br />
As for soloing and grouping, I can't recall anyone ever trying to 'KS' me actually which appears to happen every other day for everyone else. However, there are rules in the play nice policy that  imply we are supposed to... play nice.</span></td>
