				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Agro, Engagement and KSing<a name="67966"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 24 04 8:14 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Kill Stealing is defined as the killing of an NPC for any reason that is already fighting or pursuing another player or group that is prepared to engage that same NPC without that group's specific permission. 
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This is the interesting bit to me because it implys that you dont have to actually be engaged, just be prepared to engage the mob.  For example, you kite mob_01 around draining its mana to soften it up and someone takes it - this would be kill stealing because you are prepared to engage it.  Alternatively, you kite Gore around waiting for your friends to show up and someone takes her - this is not kill stealing because you are not prepared to engage it.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
